  - Recommends blended approaches combining scalable online training with context-specific, facilitated learning. Notes that effective change management for AI adoption requires transparent communication about how AI will affect roles and genuine opportunities for employees to shape implementation.

- **U.S. Government Accountability Office. (2025).** *Artificial Intelligence: Generative AI Use and Management at Federal Agencies.* GAO-25-107653.
  - Reports that generative AI use cases across federal agencies increased ninefold from 2023 to 2024. Identifies key challenges including compliance with data privacy policy and maintaining up-to-date appropriate use policies.

- **New York State Office of Information Technology Services. (2026).** *AI Training Pilot Program Results.* Albany, NY.
  - Reports that 41% of state pilot participants had no prior experience with generative AI, and 87% had received no prior training. After the pilot, overall confidence using generative AI rose by 36%. Demonstrates that structured, hands-on AI literacy programs produce measurable skill gains even among complete beginners.

